The OATH Toolkit attempts to collect several tools that are useful
when deploying technologies related to OATH.  For example, see RFC
4226 on OATH HOTP.  The components included in the package is:

   * libhotp, liboath: A shared and static C library for OATH handling.

   * hotptool, oathtool: A command line tool for generating and validating OTPs.

   * pam_hotp: A PAM module for pluggable login authentication.

See each sub-directory for more information.

For updates on the project please visit our web page:

   http://www.nongnu.org/hotp-toolkit/

For e-mail discussions related the OATH Toolkit, please send e-mail to
hotp-toolkit-help@nongnu.org after subscribing to the mailing list
through this web page:

  http://lists.nongnu.org/mailman/listinfo/hotp-toolkit-help

Note that the project used to be called "HOTP Toolkit", and there are
still several references to the old project name.
